Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the rice.

When boiling, add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{210%g}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Stir-fry until golden brown on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(diced) into small pieces.

Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm sized chunks.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1%sprig} (stalks and all).

Add the onion and green pepper to the chicken and stir fry till softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Pop your #grill{} onto high-heat for your naans.

Once the veg is soft, add the @Jalfrezi Spice Mix{1%pack} and the garlic. Cook stirring for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{1}(finely chopped) and @sugar{1} and stir together.

Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Place the @plain naans{2} under the grill and cook until toasted and golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Taste and season the curry with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, if you think it needs it and stir through half the coriander.

Fluff up the rice and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the curry and a sprinkling of coriander.

Serve with the naan. Enjoy!